    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDef_4">• A proportion is an equality between two ratios: a/b = c/d or a:b = c:d, read "a is to b as c is to d."</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefQuestion_4">If 2/5 = x/20, what is x?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerOne_4">4</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerTwo_4">8</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerThree_4">10</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_4">8</string>


    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryProperties_4">• Main rule: product of extremes = product of means (ad = bc).\n
• New proportions can be derived by combining or transforming terms.\n
• For equal ratios, (a₁ + a₂ + ... + aₙ)/(b₁ + b₂ + ... + bₙ) = a₁/b₁.</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsQuestion_4">In the proportion 3/4 = 9/d, what is d?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerOne_4">9</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_4">12</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerThree_4">16</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_4">12</string>


    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExamples_4">A car travels 180 km in 3 hours. How far does it travel in 5 hours at the same speed?\n
Step 1: Set up proportion: 180/3 = x/5.\n
Step 2: Cross multiply: 3x = 180 × 5 = 900.\n
Step 3: x = 900/3 = 300.\n
Step 4: Result: 300 km.</string>
