    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDef_4">• Key identities:\n
(a + b)² = a² + 2ab + b²\n
(a − b)² = a² − 2ab + b²\n
(a + b)(a − b) = a² − b²\n
(a ± b)³ = a³ ± 3a²b + 3ab² ± b³.\n
• Used also for approximations, e.g., (1 + a)² ≈ 1 + 2a for small a.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefQuestion_4">What is (x + 5)²?</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerOne_4">x² + 25</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerTwo_4">x² + 10x + 25</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerThree_4">x² + 5x + 25</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_4">x² + 10x + 25</string>


    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryProperties_4">Further Notes on Algebraic Identities:\n
• (a + b)² and (a − b)² always produce a perfect square trinomial.\n
• The difference of squares (a + b)(a − b) = a² − b² has no middle term.\n
• The cube identities expand to 4 terms each.\n
• These identities work in reverse for factorization: recognize the pattern, then factor.\n
• For small values of a, higher-order terms become negligible, allowing linear approximations.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsQuestion_4">What is (a + b)(a − b)?</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerOne_4">a² + b²</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_4">a² − 2ab + b²</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerThree_4">a² − b²</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_4">a² − b²</string>


    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExamples_4">Expand (2x − 3)².\n
Step 1: Apply (a − b)² = a² − 2ab + b² with a = 2x, b = 3.\n
Step 2: (2x)² − 2·(2x)·3 + 3².\n
Step 3: 4x² − 12x + 9.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExQuestion_4">What is (2x − 3)²?</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_4">4x² + 12x + 9</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_4">4x² − 12x + 9</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_4">4x² − 6x + 9</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_4">4x² − 12x + 9</string>


