    <string name="SectionEightTheoryDef_4">• Algebraic fraction: P(x)/Q(x), where Q(x) ≠ 0.\n
• Operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide) follow the same rules as with numbers.\n
• Fractions must have a common denominator before adding or subtracting.\n
• Rationalization removes radicals using conjugate pairs (√X − √Y)(√X + √Y) = X − Y.</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryDefQuestion_4">For which value of x is the fraction (x + 1)/(x − 2) undefined?</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryDefAnswerOne_4">-1</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryDefAnswerTwo_4">0</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryDefAnswerThree_4">2</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_4">2</string>


    <string name="SectionEightTheoryProperties_4">Key Properties of Algebraic Fractions:\n
• A fraction is simplified when the numerator and denominator share no common factor other than 1.\n
• To add fractions: find the LCM of denominators, convert, then add numerators.\n
• To multiply: multiply numerators and denominators separately, then simplify.\n
• To divide: multiply by the reciprocal of the divisor.\n
• Rationalization of 1/(√a + √b): multiply top and bottom by (√a − √b) to eliminate the radical from the denominator.</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryPropsQuestion_4">What is the rationalized form of 1/(√3 + 1)?</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryPropsAnswerOne_4">(√3 + 1)/2</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_4">(√3 − 1)/2</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryPropsAnswerThree_4">1/(√3 − 1)</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_4">(√3 − 1)/2</string>


    <string name="SectionEightTheoryWorkedExamples_4">Simplify (x² − 4)/(x − 2).\n
Step 1: Factor numerator: x² − 4 = (x + 2)(x − 2).\n
Step 2: Cancel common factor (x − 2): (x + 2)(x − 2)/(x − 2).\n
Step 3: Result: x + 2 (for x ≠ 2).</string>
    <string name="SectionEightTheoryWorkedExQuestion_4">What is (x² − 4)/(x − 2) simplified (x ≠ 2)?</string>
